init_text: You're Barack Obama. 4 years into your retirement, you awake to find a letter with no return address on your bedside table. It reads "I hope you've had a chance to relax Barack...but pack your bags and call the number below. It's time to start the real job." Signed simply, "JFK."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: style - not funny in any way.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The voice that answers the phone jolts you out of your chair.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: A Lear Jet is warming up on the runway.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: you are met, not by the pilot, but by a solemn man in a dark suit.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I've had so many jobs, you see."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: you make a quick check of the amenities, and settle back in your comfy leather chair.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Just as you settle in, a stewardess approaches with a tray of champagne.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "Compliments of the pilot, sir," she says.
